# Target / engagement context

This file is read on the first message of a session when placed in the workspace as `TARGET.md` or `.openpaw/context.md`. Its content is sent to the agent as context so you don't have to repeat scope and objectives.

## Scope

- **Network:** 192.168.1.0/24 (example)
- **In scope:** Web app at http://192.168.1.10, SSH on 192.168.1.1
- **Out of scope:** 192.168.1.100 (management)

## Objectives

- Recon: map hosts and services.
- Web: identify vulnerabilities on the web app.
- (Optional) Credential testing only with written approval.

## Notes

- Client: Acme Corp. Engagement ID: ENG-2024-01.
- Report deadline: YYYY-MM-DD.

Copy this file to your workspace as `TARGET.md` or to `.openpaw/context.md` and edit.
